						               													<description>From the author:&amp;#10;&amp;quot;PanzerTruppe is a set of tactical 1:1 rules for gaming WWII armored combat using 6mm micro armor and 10mm miniatures (1/300 through 1/200 scale). The basic rules comprise only a few pages of text. Optional rules are provided for advanced play involving infantry, anti-tank guns, artillery, mortars, air support, minefields, indirect fire, hedgerows, hidden set up, and more. Specifications are provided for more than 200 armored fighting vehicles covering all major nationalities from 1939 through 1945.&amp;quot;&amp;#10; From the rulebook:&amp;#10;Sequence of Play:&amp;#10;The game proceeds through the following 10 phases in order.&amp;#10;The phases are repeated&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Axis Morale &amp;amp; Load&amp;#10;     Axis Fire&amp;#10;     Axis Movement&amp;#10;     Allied Fire&amp;#10;     Axis Fire&amp;#10;     Allied Morale &amp;amp; Load&amp;#10;     Allied Fire&amp;#10;     Allied Movement&amp;#10;     Axis Fire&amp;#10;     Allied Fire&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are no &amp;quot;turns&amp;quot;, the actions of the 2 sides are interleaved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
